X = Data1.drop(columns = 'Compressive_Strenght(N/mm2)')
y = Data1['Compressive_Strenght(N/mm2)']
In [7]:
### It is better to split train and test data to prevent machine to see our data
X_train,X_test,y_train,y_test = train_test_split(X , y ,test_size=0.2 ,random_state = None, shuffle= True)
In [8]:
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
linear3 = LinearRegression()
linear3.fit(X_train,y_train)
y_pred = linear3.predict(X_test)
print('\n Linear Regression \n ')
print('Test_Score :',linear3.score(X_test, y_test))
print('Train_Score :',linear3.score(X_train, y_train))
print('Linear Coef :',linear3.coef_)
from sklearn import linear_model
ridge3 = linear_model.Ridge(normalize= True)
ridge3.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_pred = ridge3.predict(X_test)
print('\n Linear Ridge \n')
print('Test_Score :',ridge3.score(X_test, y_test))
print('Train_Score :',ridge3.score(X_train, y_train))
print('Ridge Coef :',ridge3.coef_)

from sklearn import tree
tree3 = tree.DecisionTreeRegressor(max_depth= 8)
tree3.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_pred = tree3.predict(X_test)
print('\n TreeRegressor \n')
print('Test_Score :',tree3.score(X_test, y_test))
print('Train_Score :',tree3.score(X_train, y_train))
print('Tree Coef :',tree3.feature_importances_)

nerual = MLPRegressor( hidden_layer_sizes=200)
nerual.fit(X_train , y_train)
print('\n Nerual Network \n')
print('Test Score :',nerual.score(X_test , y_test))
print('Train Score :',nerual.score(X_train , y_train))
y_pred = nerual.predict(X_test)
print('R2 Score :',r2_score(y_pred , y_test))

forest = RandomForestRegressor()
forest.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_pred = forest.predict(X_test)
print('\n RandomForest \n')
print('Test_Score :',forest.score(X_test, y_test))
print('Train_Score :',forest.score(X_train, y_train))

from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeRegressor
import sklearn.datasets as datasets
from sklearn.externals.six import StringIO
from sklearn.tree import export_graphviz
import pylab
import pandas as pd
import pydotplus
import graphviz

from IPython.display import Image
X_display = X_train
y_display = y_train

dtree = DecisionTreeRegressor(max_depth=5)
dtree.fit(X_display,y_display)

dot_data = StringIO()
export_graphviz(
    dtree, 
    out_file = dot_data,
    filled = True, 
    rounded = True,
    special_characters = True,feature_names = X.columns
)
graph_1 = pydotplus.graph_from_dot_data(dot_data.getvalue())
Image(graph_1.create_png())
